5.2. Subscriptions
Nordcurrent may provide subscription-based Services that renew automatically until cancellation, as elaborated below. Monthly subscription periods will recur each calendar month on the date of your initial purchase; provided, however, that if your initial purchase occurs on a date that is not applicable in subsequent months, the monthly subscription will recur on the last calendar day of such months. Upon cancellation of your subscription, you will retain access to your subscription benefits until the conclusion of your subscription period, after which it will expire.
You can cancel your subscription any time before the next scheduled payment to avoid further charges. If you cancel your subscription, you will not receive a refund or credit, but you can continue to access all subscription benefits through the end of your current subscription period.
Nordcurrent may change subscription plans and the price of our Service from time to time; however, any price changes or changes to your subscription plans will apply no earlier than 30 days following notice to you. If you do not wish to accept the price change or change to your subscription plan, you can cancel your subscription before the change takes effect.
If you received a discounted promotional offer, your price may increase per the terms of that offer following the initial subscription period for any subsequent renewal period.
Subscription Services may include paid subscriptions to special features. These features are subject to modification, suspension, or discontinuation at our sole discretion. Certain features may also become temporarily unavailable from time to time.
If payment is not successfully settled, due to expiration, insufficient funds, or otherwise, and you do not cancel your subscription, we may suspend your access to the subscription benefits until we have successfully charged a subscription fee. For some payment methods, the issuer may charge you certain fees, such as foreign transaction fees or other fees relating to the processing of your payment method. Local tax charges may vary depending on the payment method used. Check with your payment method service provider for details.
If you initiate a chargeback or otherwise reverse a payment, without informing Nordcurrent, we may terminate your Account immediately at our sole discretion, on the basis that you have determined that you do not want a certain subscription.
Since our Services can be utilized without a subscription, canceling your subscription won’t delete your Account. To fully terminate your Account, you must follow the Account removal process outlined in Clause 2.2.
5.2.1. External Subscriptions
If your External Service Purchase includes an automatically renewing subscription, your External Service Account will continue to be periodically charged for the subscription until you cancel. Following your initial subscription commitment period, and again after any subsequent subscription period, the subscription will automatically extend for the price and duration agreed upon during subscription.
To cancel a subscription: If you do not want your subscription to renew automatically, or if you want to change or terminate your subscription, you must log in to your External Service Account and follow instructions to manage or cancel your subscription, even if you have otherwise deleted your Account with us or if you have deleted the game from your device.
For example, if you subscribed using your Apple ID, cancellation is handled by Apple, not Nordcurrent. To cancel a subscription on an Apple device, you must visit your Apple App Store subscription settings (Settings – Apple ID – Subscriptions) and select “Cancel Subscription”, as further described at
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202039
.
Similarly, if you subscribed on Google Play, cancellation is handled by Google. To cancel a subscription on an Android device, you must visit the Google Play App’s subscription settings (Google Play – Profile – Payments & Subscriptions – Subscriptions) and select “Cancel Subscription”, as further described at
https://support.google.com/googleplay/answer/7018481?hl=en&co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid
. You can also request assistance at
Google Play
.
If you cancel a subscription, you may continue to use the canceled service until the end of your then-current subscription term. The subscription will not be renewed when your then-current term expires.
5.3.2 Internal Subscriptions
If your Internal Purchase includes an automatically renewing subscription, your selected payment method will continue to be periodically charged for the subscription until you cancel. After your initial subscription commitment period, and again after any subsequent subscription period, your subscription will automatically continue for the price and time period you agreed to when subscribing, until you cancel.
To cancel an Internal Purchase subscription, log in to the game and go to the Account section. If you cancel a subscription, you may continue to use the cancelled service until the end of your then-current subscription term. The subscription will not be renewed when your then-current term expires.
